erson I have become\r\n[03:24.49]Spread your wings and I know\r\n[03:27.36]That when God took you back, he said Hallelujah you\'re home', '/song/1649992809143.mp3', NULL);
INSERT INTO `song` VALUES (270, 69, 'Ed Sheeran- Galway Girl', '÷ (Deluxe)', '2022-04-15 11:21:00', '2022-04-15 11:21:00', '/img/songPic/song.jpg', '[00:00.000] 作词 : Ed Sheeran/Foy Vance/Johnny McDaid/Sean Graham/Amy Wadge/Niamh Dunne/Eamon Murray/Liam Bradley/Damian McKee\r\n[00:00.025] 作曲 : Ed Sheeran/Foy Vance/Johnny McDaid/Sean Graham/Amy Wadge/Niamh Dunne/Eamon Murray/Liam Bradley/Damian McKee\r\n[00:00.50]She played the fiddle in an Irish band\r\n[00:02.70]But she fell in love with an English man\r\n[00:04.92]Kissed her on the neck and then I took her by the hand\r\n[00:07.50]Said, \"Baby, I just wanna dance\"\r\n[00:09.36]I met her on Grafton street right outside of the bar\r\n[00:12.14]She shared a cigarette with me while her brother played the guitar\r\n[00:14.60]She asked me what does it mean, the Gaelic ink on your arm?\r\n[00:16.84]Said it was one of my friend\'s songs, do you want to drink on?\r\n[00:19.32]She took Jamie as a chaser, Jack for the fun\r\n[00:21.76]She got Arthur on the table, with Johnny riding as shot gun\r\n[00:24.27]Chatted some more, one more drink at the bar\r\n[00:26.54]Then put Van on the jukebox, got up to dance, you know\r\n[00:28.93]She played the fiddle in an Irish band\r\n[00:31.38]But she fell in love with an English man\r\n[00:33.71]Kissed her on the neck and then I took her by the hand\r\n[00:36.18]Said, \"Baby, I just wanna dance\"\r\n[00:38.26]With my pretty little Galway Girl\r\n[00:40.56]You\'re my pretty little Galway Girl\r\n[00:47.54]You know she beat me at darts and then she beat me at pool\r\n[00:50.59]And then she kissed me like there was nobody else in the room\r\n[00:52.93]As last orders were called was when she stood on the stool\r\n[00:55.24]After dancing the céili singing to trad tunes\r\n[00:57.83]I never heard Carrickfergus ever sung so sweet\r\n[01:00.06]Acapella in the bar using her feet for a beat\r\n[01:02.49]Oh, I could have that voice playing on repeat for a week\r\n[01:04.76]And in this packed out room swear she was singing to me\r\n[01:07.19]You know, she played the fiddle in an Irish band\r\n[01:09.84]But she fell in love with an English man\r\n[01:12.11]Kissed her on the neck and then I took her by the hand\r\n[01:14.64]Said, \"Baby, I just wanna dance\"\r\n[01:16.79]My pretty little Galway Girl\r\n[01:18.86]My, my, my, my, my, my, my Galway Girl\r\n[01:24.40]My, my, my, my, my, my, my Galway Girl\r\n[01:29.47]My, my, my, my, my, my, my Galway Girl\r\n[01:34.02]\r\n[01:35.52]Now we\'ve outstayed our welcome and it\'s closing time\r\n[01:38.46]I was holding her hand, her hand was holding mine\r\n[01:40.86]Our coats both smell of smoke, whisky and wine\r\n[01:43.33]As we fill up our lungs with the cold air of the night\r\n[01:45.71]I walked her home then she took me inside\r\n[01:48.06]Finish some Doritos and another bottle of wine\r\n[01:50.51]I swear I\'m gonna put you in a song that I write\r\n[01:52.99]About a Galway Girl and a perfect night\r\n[01:55.25]She played the fiddle in an Irish band\r\n[01:57.78]But she fell in love with an English man\r\n[02:00.11]Kissed her on the neck and then I took her by the hand\r\n[02:02.58]Said, \"Baby, I just wanna dance\"\r\n[02:04.47]My pretty little Galway Girl\r\n[02:08.41]My, my, my, my, my, my, my Galway Girl\r\n[02:12.73]My, my, my, my, my, my, my Galway Girl\r\n[02:17.77]My, my, my, my, my, my, my Galway Girl\r\n[02:23.44]', '/song/1649992860164.mp3', NULL);
